%N A137467 Least a(n) = i + j - k such that n = prime(i) + prime(j) - prime(k) >= 3, where prime(i), prime(j), and prime(k) are distinct primes.
%C A137467 Does every positive integer n admit a representation n = prime(i) + prime(j) - prime(k)?
%e A137467 For n = 6, 6 = prime(1) + prime(5) - prime(4) = 2 + 11 - 7; so a(6) = 1 + 5 - 4 = 2.
